WEBVTT

00:00:07.095 --> 00:00:08.805
here at the downtown
Radio Building...

00:00:08.805 --> 00:00:11.767
Throngs of onlookers continue
to flock in the street below

00:00:11.767 --> 00:00:13.393
in hopes of catching
a firsthand glimpse,

00:00:13.393 --> 00:00:14.728
and as no country has

00:00:14.728 --> 00:00:16.522
yet come forward to
claim the offending object,

00:00:16.522 --> 00:00:19.316
it's anyone's guess when life
here will return to normal.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:00:41.588 --> 00:00:43.548
Can we have a
moment of your time?

00:00:43.548 --> 00:00:46.969
You're, here to get a look
at the satellite I assume, yes?

00:00:46.969 --> 00:00:49.721
Could you tell our viewers at
home where you've traveled from?

00:02:41.625 --> 00:02:44.795
Wowza! Are you kidding?

00:02:48.715 --> 00:02:50.300
It's awesome!

00:02:50.300 --> 00:02:52.177
This, like, your
first beef bowl?

00:02:52.177 --> 00:02:55.597
Yep! And I gotta say: the
hype doesn't do 'em justice!

00:02:55.597 --> 00:02:58.934
Yes, well, you really ought to
try it with raw egg sometime...

00:02:58.934 --> 00:03:00.894
That is, of course,
once you've mastered

00:03:00.894 --> 00:03:03.647
this unwarrior-like
phobia of eating out alone.

00:03:07.526 --> 00:03:09.736
Daru and I only dine
together out of convenience,

00:03:09.736 --> 00:03:10.278
you understand.

00:03:10.278 --> 00:03:13.240
You're more than welcome to
join us whenever you'd like...

00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:15.826
Hey! It's comin' back to me...

00:03:15.826 --> 00:03:16.785
The last time we came here,

00:03:16.785 --> 00:03:19.121
you totally skipped out
and left me with the check!

00:03:19.121 --> 00:03:21.998
I do concede that as
a distinct possibility.

00:03:21.998 --> 00:03:23.959
Try a distinct
damn right-ability!

00:03:23.959 --> 00:03:25.794
Where're my
greenbacks, Bogart?!

00:03:25.794 --> 00:03:27.963
Not the day to bark up
that tree, I'm afraid...

00:03:27.963 --> 00:03:30.048
It's me.

00:03:30.048 --> 00:03:32.259
Kindly make the aforementioned
monetary transfers

00:03:32.259 --> 00:03:33.802
into my Swiss bank
account, if you would...

00:03:33.802 --> 00:03:35.721
That one, yes...
Wait, what?

00:03:35.721 --> 00:03:36.304
The Organization
is playing havoc...

00:03:36.304 --> 00:03:38.348
Please. No. Cell-phones.

00:03:38.348 --> 00:03:41.017
Er, does it count if the
conversation's all in his head?

00:03:41.017 --> 00:03:42.227
Too-too-roo!

00:03:44.354 --> 00:03:46.440
I didn't know you were
part of the group now.

00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:48.733
Oh, I was just on the
ol' lunch break, you know...

00:03:48.733 --> 00:03:50.235
You'd should've
come around earlier,

00:03:50.235 --> 00:03:51.778
it would have been a party.

00:03:51.778 --> 00:03:53.947
I propose we do this
again tomorrow, all of us.

00:03:53.947 --> 00:03:55.449
Okarin's treat.

00:03:55.449 --> 00:03:57.075
No no no. Don't put me on hold!

00:03:57.075 --> 00:03:57.826
Crisis or not,

00:03:57.826 --> 00:04:00.328
it can't take the banks a full
week to straggle back online...!

00:04:00.328 --> 00:04:02.080
Cool, the gang's all here!

00:04:03.415 --> 00:04:05.751
Double-O Four.
Well-rested, I trust?

00:04:05.751 --> 00:04:07.502
Don't start with
that crap again.

00:04:13.467 --> 00:04:15.385
Hey. I hate to break
up your meeting...

00:04:15.385 --> 00:04:17.929
but your lunch break
ended five minutes ago.

00:04:20.891 --> 00:04:22.142
What's that about?

00:04:23.268 --> 00:04:24.728
Round table?

00:04:24.728 --> 00:04:25.103
Yep.

00:04:25.103 --> 00:04:26.897
That like a thing...?

00:04:26.897 --> 00:04:28.982
A lab member
pow-wow, indeed.

00:04:28.982 --> 00:04:31.109
You make it sound like
we do 'em all the time.

00:04:31.109 --> 00:04:34.446
Only table I see
here is rectangular.

00:04:34.446 --> 00:04:36.281
Ugh. I don't mean it literally;

00:04:36.281 --> 00:04:38.200
"round table" is simply
a figure of speech;

00:04:38.200 --> 00:04:39.618
meant to evoke camaraderie--

00:04:39.618 --> 00:04:41.995
Thank you. I'm quite
familiar with the expression.

00:04:41.995 --> 00:04:45.123
I'm just never sure whether you
mean things literally or not.

00:04:45.123 --> 00:04:47.709
I think it sounds sweet
even if it is rectangular.

00:04:47.709 --> 00:04:48.835
Thank you...

00:04:48.835 --> 00:04:51.338
You're welcome...!
So let's start...

00:04:51.338 --> 00:04:53.465
Who's gonna bring
the "camaraderie"?

00:04:53.465 --> 00:04:56.426
Yeah, what now, chief?
You pull a sword from a stone?

00:04:56.426 --> 00:04:58.261
I'd like to point out
that as a temporary member

00:04:58.261 --> 00:04:59.679
I shouldn't be
eligible to attend.

00:04:59.679 --> 00:05:01.556
Oh my goodness... Fine!

00:05:01.556 --> 00:05:04.643
I grant you special
privileges... Moving on.

00:05:04.643 --> 00:05:08.480
Our needs must be to apprise
Mayuri of notre dilemme.

00:05:08.480 --> 00:05:10.065
Uh oh. What's that?

00:05:16.655 --> 00:05:18.907
In short, my minions,
if we intend

00:05:18.907 --> 00:05:21.493
to nip SERN's odious design
in the proverbial bud,

00:05:21.493 --> 00:05:23.745
perfecting the Phone
Wave (Real Name TBA)'s

00:05:23.745 --> 00:05:26.456
incipient functionality
is absolutely paramount.

00:05:26.456 --> 00:05:28.917
Awww, you use so many big words

00:05:28.917 --> 00:05:31.044
the little ones around them
don't make sense either.

00:05:31.044 --> 00:05:34.506
Let me put it this way then,
SERN is very, very bad.

00:05:34.506 --> 00:05:36.925
'Kay, but what do you mean
by perfecting it, though?

00:05:36.925 --> 00:05:37.926
I mean...

00:05:37.926 --> 00:05:40.095
We already sent texts back in
time, what else do you think--?

00:05:40.095 --> 00:05:42.472
True, but in point of fact,
we've only done so twice!

00:05:42.472 --> 00:05:47.102
Flying blind, I might add. No.
We have to look for patterns.

00:05:47.102 --> 00:05:49.187
Well then, we know
from the last experiment

00:05:49.187 --> 00:05:52.107
it only seems to work when
there's an electrical discharge.

00:05:53.692 --> 00:05:54.442
Eureka!

00:05:54.442 --> 00:05:56.695
Flash of inspiration?

00:05:56.695 --> 00:05:59.739
No, it's just that "Mail From
the Past" is too inelegant...

00:05:59.739 --> 00:06:02.576
If we expect to be inspired
we must first christen

00:06:02.576 --> 00:06:04.077
the phenomena
with a decent name.

00:06:04.077 --> 00:06:06.121
How 'bout...
Cart before the horse?

00:06:06.121 --> 00:06:08.498
Not helpful!
Continue to mock me,

00:06:08.498 --> 00:06:09.207
and my wrath shall
hamme--

00:06:09.207 --> 00:06:09.791
Please.

00:06:09.791 --> 00:06:12.002
You'd get sidetracked thinking
up a name for a screwdriver.

00:06:12.002 --> 00:06:14.963
Excuse me! Prepare to
eat your words, nay-sayer.

00:06:14.963 --> 00:06:17.007
I've already plucked a name
for the facts in question,

00:06:17.007 --> 00:06:18.008
as if from thin air!

00:06:18.008 --> 00:06:21.845
We shall call it:
Kyouma's Nostalgia Drive!

00:06:26.182 --> 00:06:28.935
I, propose referring
to it as KND for short.

00:06:28.935 --> 00:06:31.021
Catchy anagrams are
far more marketable--

00:06:31.021 --> 00:06:32.647
Sounds like a fast food chain.

00:06:32.647 --> 00:06:35.108
Duly noted, temporary assistant!

00:06:35.108 --> 00:06:35.984
Now if you'll just let...

00:06:35.984 --> 00:06:37.652
I say we have a
show of hands...

00:06:37.652 --> 00:06:40.447
Who here is good with
"Kyouma's Nostalgia Drive?"

00:06:42.282 --> 00:06:43.950
Come on! Neither of you?!

00:06:43.950 --> 00:06:46.578
Sorry, I agree with her.
It's not a bad name...

00:06:46.578 --> 00:06:47.787
But even when you don't

00:06:47.787 --> 00:06:49.831
use the letters it makes
me think of a charity.

00:06:49.831 --> 00:06:52.542
Yeah. 'sides,
"Kyouma"? Nice try.

00:06:52.542 --> 00:06:54.878
In the interest of keeping
it cute and simple...

00:06:54.878 --> 00:06:57.005
Since it goes against
the flow of time,

00:06:57.005 --> 00:06:58.965
why not call it
"contrary-mail."

00:06:58.965 --> 00:07:00.383
I don't get it.

00:07:00.383 --> 00:07:02.552
You have a lot to
learn about "cute."

00:07:02.552 --> 00:07:03.678
Why are we arguing

00:07:03.678 --> 00:07:06.348
when it should clearly be "The
Mail That Leapt Through Time"?

00:07:06.348 --> 00:07:08.391
Because we're not entering
it into a film festival.

00:07:08.391 --> 00:07:09.893
Now you're just being a brat.

00:07:09.893 --> 00:07:11.478
At least my idea
doesn't make you

00:07:11.478 --> 00:07:12.604
wanna order a bucket
of chicken wings!

00:07:12.604 --> 00:07:14.731
Balance, man! We need
romance and concision!

00:07:14.731 --> 00:07:16.566
Then I'll squish it to
"Time Leaper..."

00:07:16.566 --> 00:07:19.444
Except that now we don't
know what's leaping, do we?

00:07:19.444 --> 00:07:21.529
Maybe we could work
"banana" in there somewhere?

00:07:21.529 --> 00:07:22.864
Ah! Can you
imagine our logo?!

00:07:22.864 --> 00:07:24.199
Too-too-roo!

00:07:24.199 --> 00:07:26.284
Ha...! Just wait till you
get a load of this one...!

00:07:26.284 --> 00:07:29.412
We call it...
"Flux Mail Capacitor."

00:07:29.412 --> 00:07:31.998
Are we implying that it
runs on plutonium now?

00:07:31.998 --> 00:07:34.000
Ooo! Ooo!
"DeLorean Mail"...!

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.251
That doesn't make sense.

00:07:35.251 --> 00:07:36.294
Close enough...

00:07:36.294 --> 00:07:38.254
Though, if we go with that,

00:07:38.254 --> 00:07:42.008
I'd suggest we
shorten it to "D-Mail."

00:07:42.008 --> 00:07:44.010
Oh! That's a good one!

00:07:44.010 --> 00:07:46.805
Great. We can move on. Finally.

00:07:46.805 --> 00:07:50.350
We now begin our experiments
with D-Mail (Real Name TBA)...

00:07:50.350 --> 00:07:52.435
Drop the TBA. We've got it.

00:07:52.435 --> 00:07:54.604
Fine. I dub this
Operation Wyrd--

00:07:54.604 --> 00:07:56.856
You can drop that, too.

00:07:56.856 --> 00:07:57.982
I'd like to get
back to the whole

00:07:57.982 --> 00:08:00.068
"we don't have a clue
what's happening" issue.

00:08:00.068 --> 00:08:02.445
I mean, we're pretty sure the
electrical surges are related,

00:08:02.445 --> 00:08:03.738
but that's about it.

00:08:03.738 --> 00:08:06.783
Precisely what we've gathered
here to establish, Hack...

00:08:06.783 --> 00:08:09.703
Thanks to my genius, however,
we're not shooting in the dark.

00:08:09.703 --> 00:08:11.663
You, dear cohorts,
have overlooked

00:08:11.663 --> 00:08:14.124
the simplest yet most
crucial condition involved...

00:08:14.124 --> 00:08:17.460
To wit: Time!

00:08:17.460 --> 00:08:19.629
The first D-Mail made
its apparent leap backward

00:08:19.629 --> 00:08:20.922
between noon and one o'clock;

00:08:20.922 --> 00:08:22.090
the second at approximately
six in the evening.

00:08:22.090 --> 00:08:24.217
Thus... if we conduct
our experiments

00:08:24.217 --> 00:08:26.219
so that the same
windows are observed,

00:08:26.219 --> 00:08:28.346
success is a
strong likelihood.

00:08:28.346 --> 00:08:29.472
Dude. If it were that easy

00:08:29.472 --> 00:08:31.099
you think we'd be the
ones to discover it?

00:08:31.099 --> 00:08:33.268
If you can do
better I'm all ears.

00:08:33.268 --> 00:08:34.352
Mayuri! Banana me!

00:08:34.352 --> 00:08:37.480
We're running kind of
low on the test subjects...

00:08:37.480 --> 00:08:39.524
We could just use
something else, couldn't we?

00:08:39.524 --> 00:08:41.192
Maybe a cucumber...

00:08:41.192 --> 00:08:43.695
Hack! This is hardly
the time... No.

00:08:43.695 --> 00:08:45.780
The effect on bananas
classifies as a known.

00:08:45.780 --> 00:08:48.116
So, if you'd be so good as
to insert what we have left...

00:08:48.116 --> 00:08:49.242
"Insert..."

00:08:49.242 --> 00:08:52.746
Oh, grow up...! I swear...

00:08:52.746 --> 00:08:53.621
I'm sorry, sweetie...

00:08:53.621 --> 00:08:55.248
Look, I promise to
buy you some more

00:08:55.248 --> 00:08:56.374
as soon as we're done here.

00:08:56.374 --> 00:08:57.292
Aw, really...?!

00:08:57.292 --> 00:09:00.003
These two guys never
buy me anything.

00:09:00.003 --> 00:09:03.006
It's gonna be awesome having
you around the lab, I can tell!

00:09:04.090 --> 00:09:05.508
Oww!

00:09:05.508 --> 00:09:06.885
Please... Enough
with the show-boating.

00:09:06.885 --> 00:09:08.595
Shut up.

00:09:09.679 --> 00:09:11.556
Leave my friend alone, ouchies.

00:09:11.556 --> 00:09:13.099
Oh, it's not that bad.

00:09:13.099 --> 00:09:15.143
Put away the tea
set, Princess Ow.

00:09:15.143 --> 00:09:16.936
There's work to do.
Send me a text.

00:09:16.936 --> 00:09:18.188
Okay, okay.

00:09:18.188 --> 00:09:20.732
Minute thirty
good for the timer?

00:09:20.732 --> 00:09:23.693
Yes... Commence Operation Wyrd!

00:09:31.409 --> 00:09:33.369
Now!

00:09:37.999 --> 00:09:41.169
Yes... That's it!
Show me what you've got!

00:09:43.296 --> 00:09:45.965
The fruit is where?!

00:09:45.965 --> 00:09:47.717
It's a gel-nana, it worked!

00:09:47.717 --> 00:09:48.676
Whoa...

00:09:52.013 --> 00:09:53.389
Just as I hypothesized!

00:09:53.389 --> 00:09:55.391
Time of day is an
essential component

00:09:55.391 --> 00:09:56.851
in how the D-Mail system works!

00:09:56.851 --> 00:09:57.811
I am a genius!

00:09:57.811 --> 00:09:58.978
Nice job, Okabe.

00:09:58.978 --> 00:10:01.856
I, was kind of inclined to
doubt you at first, but...

00:10:01.856 --> 00:10:03.316
Forgiven...

00:10:03.316 --> 00:10:04.359
It is quite enough to see that

00:10:04.359 --> 00:10:07.695
you are appropriately
awed by my intellect.

00:10:07.695 --> 00:10:10.573
Whatever. Did you get the text?

00:10:10.573 --> 00:10:14.369
Indeed... Five days ago,
to be exact.

00:10:14.369 --> 00:10:15.453
Yeah, but there's two.

00:10:15.453 --> 00:10:16.746
Did you send another one?

00:10:16.746 --> 00:10:18.873
Nuh-uh. Just the one.

00:10:21.751 --> 00:10:24.420
Interesting. It's been split up.

00:10:24.420 --> 00:10:26.798
I'm not familiar
with this vernacular.

00:10:29.133 --> 00:10:31.177
In America it's a compliment.

00:10:32.595 --> 00:10:34.097
You know, now
that I think about it,

00:10:34.097 --> 00:10:36.724
your D-mail to me the other
day was all broken up, too.

00:10:36.724 --> 00:10:39.018
Part of it was cut off,
as a matter of fact.

00:10:39.018 --> 00:10:42.355
And 'course it popped
up five days earlier...

00:10:42.355 --> 00:10:45.483
I know, right? Probably
some physical... law...

00:10:45.483 --> 00:10:47.986
Wait that would mean
my head's full of air...

00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:51.281
There is no way
that's a compliment!

00:10:51.281 --> 00:10:52.532
How are you just
now getting that?

00:10:52.532 --> 00:10:56.786
That vile little minx and her
infernal insults...! Blast!

00:10:56.786 --> 00:10:58.454
Are you stocking up
for the end of times...?

00:10:58.454 --> 00:11:00.748
Ramen and one--one--bag
of paraffin chocolate

00:11:00.748 --> 00:11:01.708
is more than enough.

00:11:01.708 --> 00:11:04.127
It looks like you're
amping up for a bender.

00:11:04.127 --> 00:11:06.462
What, a guy can't celebrate
a successful experiment?

00:11:06.462 --> 00:11:07.755
Put em back, lard silo.

00:11:07.755 --> 00:11:09.424
Screw. You.

00:11:26.232 --> 00:11:27.650
My god...

00:11:28.902 --> 00:11:31.905
I was so excited about our
success I neglected to weigh

00:11:31.905 --> 00:11:33.948
the reality of what
we've uncovered here...

00:11:36.117 --> 00:11:38.494
Mayuri's knee deep
in this, too...

00:11:38.912 --> 00:11:40.830
Why on earth did I tell her?

00:11:53.885 --> 00:11:56.721
Well, if it isn't my old
pen pal Shining Finger.

00:12:00.808 --> 00:12:02.518
Yes, hi.

00:12:06.564 --> 00:12:09.734
What is wrong with you?
I'm right here.

00:12:09.734 --> 00:12:12.195
Where... where's your phone?

00:12:12.195 --> 00:12:14.072
Well, I'd tell you
if you were authorized

00:12:14.072 --> 00:12:16.074
to be briefed on the
epoch-ushering experiment

00:12:16.074 --> 00:12:17.825
it is currently central to...

00:12:17.825 --> 00:12:19.243
Ready when you are.

00:12:20.244 --> 00:12:22.080
Um, boss...?

00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:23.873
Who's this spank worthy--

00:12:23.873 --> 00:12:26.292
Er, I mean, totally respectable
young meatspace angel

00:12:26.292 --> 00:12:28.002
with the knock-out
ass in front of me?

00:12:28.002 --> 00:12:29.712
How rude of me.

00:12:29.712 --> 00:12:33.549
Daru, meet Kiryuu Moeka,
a.k.a. Shining Finger.

00:12:33.549 --> 00:12:35.176
Hello there, my lovely lady...

00:12:41.224 --> 00:12:43.226
And just like that,
a man's drop-kicked

00:12:43.226 --> 00:12:46.562
back into the shady underworld
of all-night RPGs...

00:12:49.607 --> 00:12:51.192
Yo...! Check it...!

00:12:51.901 --> 00:12:54.696
You party people bringin'
the ruckus or what?

00:12:54.696 --> 00:12:55.905
In a manner of speaking.

00:12:55.905 --> 00:12:58.408
Our researches will indeed
bring, as you say, the--

00:12:58.408 --> 00:13:00.868
Yeah, that's real
crunk and all, but...

00:13:00.868 --> 00:13:03.329
Papa Bald Cap is seriously
pissed off at you guys...

00:13:03.329 --> 00:13:06.457
Says the vibrations from your
floor are givin' him migraines.

00:13:06.457 --> 00:13:09.085
"You want your rent to give
you a damn migraine?!"...

00:13:09.085 --> 00:13:10.461
I can't do the voice,
but you get it.

00:13:10.461 --> 00:13:13.756
Damn it all...! Hack!

00:13:13.756 --> 00:13:16.634
Run upstairs and tell the girls
to suspend all experimentation.

00:13:16.634 --> 00:13:18.094
I'll try and
sweet-talk the cur.

00:13:18.094 --> 00:13:19.804
Roger. I'm on top of it...

00:13:19.804 --> 00:13:21.347
good luck not getting evicted.

00:13:23.433 --> 00:13:25.518
Is Makise Kurisu
still up there?

00:13:25.518 --> 00:13:28.229
Huh? She is.
But I don't understand

00:13:28.229 --> 00:13:30.690
what that could
possibly mean to you...

00:13:30.690 --> 00:13:31.941
Why were you giving
her the evil eye...?

00:13:31.941 --> 00:13:36.154
What happened in your past?

00:13:36.154 --> 00:13:38.781
Nothing happened in the past.

00:13:38.781 --> 00:13:40.700
I see it now:
you were turtle fishing

00:13:40.700 --> 00:13:42.744
and she carelessly let
slip through her fingers

00:13:42.744 --> 00:13:44.704
the finest red-eared
slider ever--

00:13:44.704 --> 00:13:47.540
Stop it! I'd never
seen her before!

00:13:47.540 --> 00:13:49.333
Why are you here
gabbin' with me anyway?

00:13:49.333 --> 00:13:51.502
Shouldn't you be groveling?

00:13:54.255 --> 00:13:55.465
I don't know what
you're doing up there

00:13:55.465 --> 00:13:56.883
and I don't wanna know...

00:13:56.883 --> 00:14:00.470
But if it involves an elephant,
you're in breach of your lease.

00:14:00.470 --> 00:14:03.347
Well, I can assure you
sir it is not a pachyderm,

00:14:03.347 --> 00:14:05.308
though it is definitely huge.

00:14:05.308 --> 00:14:09.312
Not to worry, though.
You'll be vexed no more today--

00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:14.150
Why aren't you stopping?

00:14:20.114 --> 00:14:22.742
Did I or did I not give
you orders to desist?!

00:14:22.742 --> 00:14:25.453
Hey, I told them to.
She's the one who kept on.

00:14:25.453 --> 00:14:27.371
I sent you another one.
Did it go through?

00:14:27.371 --> 00:14:28.998
How am I supposed to know?!

00:14:28.998 --> 00:14:31.084
You had your phone
on you five days ago.

00:14:31.084 --> 00:14:31.834
Stop mocking--

00:14:31.834 --> 00:14:33.503
Oh, that's right;
your phone rang

00:14:33.503 --> 00:14:35.254
like a bazillion times
while you were gone.

00:14:35.254 --> 00:14:37.298
Even when we
weren't running tests.

00:14:41.010 --> 00:14:44.013
She's was five feet
from me for half of these!

00:14:44.013 --> 00:14:44.972
Who're you mad at?

00:14:44.972 --> 00:14:48.267
Oh, just ignore him, hon.
He's running low on calcium.

00:14:48.267 --> 00:14:49.185
I am not!

00:14:49.185 --> 00:14:51.938
I realize you're preoccupied,
but if you think it's important,

00:14:51.938 --> 00:14:53.397
I gleaned enough
data to work up

00:14:53.397 --> 00:14:55.608
a rough sketch of
how D-Mail works.

00:14:55.608 --> 00:14:56.818
What?!

00:14:58.611 --> 00:15:01.364
I've calculated that one
second on the timer equals

00:15:01.364 --> 00:15:02.907
an hour in reality,

00:15:02.907 --> 00:15:04.742
moving upstream to the
flow of linear time...

00:15:04.742 --> 00:15:08.454
That means a minute
thirty translates to five days.

00:15:08.454 --> 00:15:09.872
Pretty balls-out
she locked on to

00:15:09.872 --> 00:15:12.291
how to control the distance
a text travels back, huh?

00:15:12.291 --> 00:15:14.377
Indeed. But being limited
to thirty-six characters

00:15:14.377 --> 00:15:16.003
is still our Achilles' Heel.

00:15:16.003 --> 00:15:17.463
I'd like to find a way
to improve on that,

00:15:17.463 --> 00:15:18.881
if at all possible...

00:15:18.881 --> 00:15:20.883
As it stands now,
it's not very practical.

00:15:20.883 --> 00:15:22.885
Well, that's not such a big
deal if you don't have

00:15:22.885 --> 00:15:24.971
to send anything really
large back in time...

00:15:24.971 --> 00:15:27.890
Hey, maybe it's hard because of
the whole Car Black Hole thing.

00:15:27.890 --> 00:15:29.517
I think you mean,
"Kerr" Black Hole.

00:15:29.517 --> 00:15:30.268
That's it.

00:15:30.268 --> 00:15:32.520
A Kerr Black Hole is too
tight to let big stuff through.

00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:35.189
Maybe it just needs a
little, uh. practice...

00:15:35.189 --> 00:15:36.774
Will you knock it off?!

00:15:36.774 --> 00:15:37.984
I suggest rest.

00:15:37.984 --> 00:15:40.403
We can hit the problem
with fresh minds tomorrow...

00:15:40.403 --> 00:15:42.613
Each of us should
feel proud of what's

00:15:42.613 --> 00:15:44.157
been accomplished here today.

00:15:44.157 --> 00:15:47.451
Because of us,
August 2, 2010 is now a date

00:15:47.451 --> 00:15:49.704
that will live in the
hearts of mankind forever!

00:15:49.704 --> 00:15:52.039
On this day, the
Future Gadget Laboratory

00:15:52.039 --> 00:15:55.084
breathed new life into a
dream as old as the hills...

00:15:56.169 --> 00:15:58.588
For we have bridled time!

00:16:00.506 --> 00:16:03.676
Well, except that SERN
kind of already beat us to it...

00:16:03.676 --> 00:16:06.220
And saying we've bridled
it is presumptuous.

00:16:06.220 --> 00:16:08.764
We're still stuck in
the preliminary phase.

00:16:08.764 --> 00:16:11.142
I am attempting
to be poetic here...!

00:16:11.142 --> 00:16:12.852
Must you insist on
sapping the thunder

00:16:12.852 --> 00:16:13.936
out of every single utterance?!

00:16:13.936 --> 00:16:15.771
Okarin...

00:16:15.771 --> 00:16:18.816
I'm super proud of what
we've all accomplished here.

00:16:36.292 --> 00:16:37.835
Where am I?

00:16:44.467 --> 00:16:47.303
Don't panic.
You're not the one moving.

00:16:49.972 --> 00:16:52.892
Time and space have
switched places here.

00:16:54.894 --> 00:16:57.647
So this is an event horizon...

00:16:57.647 --> 00:16:59.690
Space can no longer
be moved through,

00:16:59.690 --> 00:17:04.403
and time as you understand
it ceases to exist.

00:17:04.403 --> 00:17:05.196
One second to you,

00:17:05.196 --> 00:17:08.908
for me stretches out past the
horizon line of what is real.

00:17:08.908 --> 00:17:11.285
Are you saying that
space has fallen away?

00:17:11.285 --> 00:17:13.246
That time has no part of it?

00:17:14.747 --> 00:17:18.584
What's moving, then?
Me, or the universe?

00:17:18.584 --> 00:17:22.213
Don't look back...
Eternity isn't infinite...

00:17:22.213 --> 00:17:25.883
Reality has a
beginning and an end...

00:17:25.883 --> 00:17:28.886
Always has. Always will.

00:17:35.226 --> 00:17:39.230
If that's true...
Where does that leave me?

00:17:39.230 --> 00:17:42.733
Move forward...
Look over the edge.

00:17:54.287 --> 00:17:59.750
You're on my last nerve...
For cryin' out loud get a life.

00:17:59.750 --> 00:18:02.128
"Sorry about yesterday."

00:18:02.128 --> 00:18:04.714
"I really need to drop by
and talk to you soon."

00:18:05.506 --> 00:18:07.758
Does it not occur to
you that people sleep?

00:18:10.428 --> 00:18:12.638
Well who the Hell
wouldn't be at this hour?!

00:18:12.638 --> 00:18:15.182
What?

00:18:31.365 --> 00:18:34.285
Seriously? I'm right here.

00:18:35.745 --> 00:18:38.164
Ugh. Whatever it
is, just say it...

00:18:38.164 --> 00:18:40.958
Look, this is getting ridiculous
and it's very early...

00:18:40.958 --> 00:18:43.002
Wait, is this your idea
of hounding yours truly

00:18:43.002 --> 00:18:45.963
for an exclusive
interview or something?

00:18:45.963 --> 00:18:48.090
Why won't you speak?

00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:49.842
Oh, of course...

00:18:50.509 --> 00:18:54.180
The aura of big, bad, legendary
mad scientist Hououin Kyouma

00:18:54.180 --> 00:18:58.142
robs yet another innocent
lamb of her powers of speech!

00:18:58.142 --> 00:19:01.687
It's just... easier...
sending texts...

00:19:01.687 --> 00:19:07.693
I came here... to... uh... well,
you know... see the... IBN.

00:19:07.693 --> 00:19:10.988
Very well... But see
is all you shall do...

00:19:10.988 --> 00:19:13.908
That done, you will
leave at once. Understood?

00:19:28.297 --> 00:19:29.131
Maybe she's just part

00:19:29.131 --> 00:19:31.842
of what Daru calls
the "antiquing crowd."

00:19:37.014 --> 00:19:38.557
Feel free, but beware...

00:19:38.557 --> 00:19:39.600
Photograph my face

00:19:39.600 --> 00:19:42.228
and you'll leave me no
choice but to silence--

00:19:47.024 --> 00:19:48.567
You expect me to
let you borrow it?

00:19:48.567 --> 00:19:50.528
And help you haul it?

00:19:50.528 --> 00:19:53.614
What part of "look only" do you
fail to comprehend, my dear?

00:19:53.614 --> 00:19:54.740
Besides, if you
intend to make off

00:19:54.740 --> 00:19:59.120
with it you could at least do me
the kindness of asking out loud.

00:19:59.120 --> 00:20:01.914
May I please... uh... borrow it?

00:20:02.957 --> 00:20:04.792
I'm afraid you're
out of luck there...

00:20:04.792 --> 00:20:07.169
I myself only have it
on loan for an interval

00:20:07.169 --> 00:20:08.212
from a trusted friend...

00:20:08.212 --> 00:20:09.922
I am honor-bound to return it

00:20:09.922 --> 00:20:12.800
once my researches
are at an end.

00:20:12.800 --> 00:20:14.927
So... who did you
borrow it from?

00:20:14.927 --> 00:20:16.887
Some friends from
the Yanabayashi Shrine.

00:20:16.887 --> 00:20:19.348
Good morrow, my peeps!

00:20:19.348 --> 00:20:23.018
Oh... Hey I didn't
realize we had a guest.

00:20:23.018 --> 00:20:25.229
Ah. You recall my
friend from yesterday...

00:20:25.229 --> 00:20:26.939
This rotund fellow
is nothing less

00:20:26.939 --> 00:20:29.817
than my right hand man,
our good hack, Daru.

00:20:29.817 --> 00:20:31.527
Hacker, thank you very much.

00:20:31.527 --> 00:20:33.988
Had a couple ideas
how we might tart up

00:20:33.988 --> 00:20:35.614
the Phone Wave a
notch, by the way.

00:20:35.614 --> 00:20:38.033
I mean it's such
an ass-pain as is.

00:20:38.033 --> 00:20:40.327
Some serious tweakage
is needed if we're gonna

00:20:40.327 --> 00:20:42.788
make sendin' mail to the past
user friendly, am I right?

00:20:47.334 --> 00:20:50.254
Uh... Yes... You misheard him...

00:20:50.254 --> 00:20:52.256
He, didn't say
"sending mail to the past,"

00:20:52.256 --> 00:20:55.259
he said "Kending
eorfals du cree clast."

00:20:55.259 --> 00:20:56.427
Ancient Sumerian, you see.

00:20:56.427 --> 00:20:58.137
Yes, yes. Roughly translated,

00:20:58.137 --> 00:20:59.889
it means "would you
care for an omelet?"

00:20:59.889 --> 00:21:01.223
Good morning, Okarin...!

00:21:01.223 --> 00:21:02.725
Mind if I heat up
my chicken tenders

00:21:02.725 --> 00:21:05.603
before you start your
time travel experiments?

00:21:05.603 --> 00:21:06.979
Morning everyone.

00:21:06.979 --> 00:21:08.439
I think I had an "ah-ha" moment

00:21:08.439 --> 00:21:10.900
about the time
machine last night.

00:21:12.776 --> 00:21:14.987
It's me... Situation critical...

00:21:14.987 --> 00:21:18.782
No, no... An outsider's
caught wind of numero eight...

00:21:18.782 --> 00:21:19.658
Yes, of course I'll handle it.

00:21:19.658 --> 00:21:21.160
Okay, what is it this time?

00:21:21.160 --> 00:21:23.662
Apparently it involves
ignoring the three of us.

00:21:23.662 --> 00:21:26.624
...the Organization know we're
performing experiments simi--

00:21:26.624 --> 00:21:29.168
Damn it all, I'm trying
to have a conversation!

00:21:29.168 --> 00:21:30.503
Is it true?

00:21:37.426 --> 00:21:39.553
F... B?

00:21:47.811 --> 00:21:51.816
Very well... I guess since
the cat's out of the bag...

00:21:52.775 --> 00:21:55.528
I'm loath to do this, however...

00:21:55.528 --> 00:21:56.946
Kiryuu Moeka...

00:21:56.946 --> 00:22:01.116
As of this moment, I christen
you lab member Double-O Five!

